####################################################

Code developed by: Andres Florez (Los Andes), Alfredo Gurrola (Vanderbilt) and Amandeep Kalsi (Panjab)

###################################################

The recipe is to install the code at LPC/ACCRE. 
Therefore, to install the code elsewere, you'd need 
to make the necessary changes.

In order to use the code you need to follow carefully these steps:


#####################################################################
#                         CMSSW_8_0_10 Recipe                        #
#####################################################################

1. You need to work at the SLC6 area.

   setenv SCRAM_ARCH slc6_amd64_gcc530
   source /cvmfs/cms.cern.ch/cmsset_default.csh

2. set the CMSSW release: cmsrel CMSSW_8_0_10

3. cd CMSSW_8_0_10/src

4. cmsenv

5. Install and compile the code to use the MET producers (for covariance matrix):

  6.1 git cms-init
  6.2 git cms-addpkg RecoMET/METProducers
  6.3 scram b -j 10
  6.4 git cms-merge-topic -u cms-met:CMSSW_8_0_X-METFilterUpdate
  6.5 scram b -j 10

6. Get the NTupleMaker code and compile it:

  7.1 git clone https://github.com/florez/NtupleMaker_740
  7.2 cd NtupleMaker_740
  7.3 git checkout for_CMSSW_8X 
  7.4 cd ../
  7.5 mv NtupleMaker_740 NtupleMaker
  7.6 scram b -j 10

8. In the python directory, there is file called miniAODv2_8010_25ns_*.py (name specifies which file is appropriate)
   8.1 You can run it with CMSSW (make sure it runs on a valid miniOADv2): cmsRun miniAODv2_8010_25ns_MC.py
